deck: A powerfull blind russian telepath, father of Michele Silenzi [protagonist of the "Il Ragazzo Invisibile" Film].
description:
History

After receiving specials powers after the exposure to radiation for a nuclear central breakdown in Russia, Andreij, alongsite with many others, have been imprisoned into "La Cittadella degli Speciali" [The Citadel of Specials], a City Sized prison in Siberia, where the Soviet Government start to study them.

While in prison, he meet a girl named Yelena, also a Special, and the two fall in love.

With the crumble of the Sovient in Russia, the Specials rebel and take the City of Specials, transforming into their revolutionary base. Andreij, Yelena and some others don't accept the new leadership and try to escape, prefering to be free instead than imprisoned under some sort of "Revolutionary Special Leader"

While Yelena was supposed dead in the escape, Andreij leave Russia with is newborn son, the first "born special", and after giving him to a young italian cop, Giovanna Silenzi, for hiding from the Divisione ("Division", the organizzation that now rule the City of Specials), continue his run along the europe, only to return in Italy 13 years after, for reveal the truth to his son Michele.

Andreij is a powerfull telepath, able to read many minds at the same time and erase selected memory from great group of people, but as all other Special, his powers are corrupting is body, and he start to lose his sight till become totally blind.

SPOILER:

In the end of the film and the comic, is revealed that Andreij and Yelena have not one but two twin sons, a boy and a girl, and the where Andreij have hidden his daughter is still unknown

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic.

IN OTHER MEDIA:

Andreij is played by bulgarian actor Christo Jivkov
name: Andreji

deck: Michele Silenzi, a.k.a. "Il Ragazzo Invisibile" (Italian for "The Invisible Boy), is the main character of the film with same name, with the power of turn itself invisible
description:
History

Michele is a 13 years shiy boy, grown up in Trieste, Italy, son of Giovanna Silenzi and another cop who died in service while Michele was a child. But this truth will crumble to dust when Michele discover having the power of turning itself invisible, and a misterious organization called "La Divisione" [The Division] start to kidnap boys and girls at his school.

Meeting a strange blind man called Andreij, he discover the truth: Giovanna is only his adoptive mother, having received him from Andreij when he have only few months, and he is in reality the son of two superpowered russian fugitive. Giovanna raised him as his son, faking all the document on his birth, for saving him from "La Divisione", which was chasing Andreij, while his true mother was presumed dead

Shocked by the truth, Michele must learn to use his powers, and with Giovanna, Andreij and some friends, must stop La Divisione from capturing him and free the other kidnapped student (among which there is Stella Morrison, the girl he love).

The constume he use have been created by La Divisione years ago, based on the power of the true mother of Michele, Yelena, which showed the same invisibility powers.

In the end of the film, Andeij erase the memory of anyone have discovered the powers of Michele (included Stella) for covering is secret identity.

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic. The major part of his history is showed in the Film "Il Ragazzo Invisibile", while in the comics he is only a minor character, since the comics is focused on his true parents.

IN OTHER MEDIA:

Michele Silenzi is played by young italian actor Ludovico Girardello
name: Michele Silenzi

deck: Russian "Special" with invisibility and telekinesis powers, she is the true mother of Michele Silenzi, the Invisible Boy
description:
History

Receiving special powers after the exposure to radiation for a nuclear central breakdown in Russia, Yelena, alongsite with many others, have been imprisoned into "La Cittadella degli Speciali" [The Citadel of Specials], a City Sized prison in Siberia, where the Soviet Government start to study them.

The first years of Yelena in prison are not known, but when he meet a man named Andreij, also a Special, and the two fall in love. She was one of the most promising "Special" in the Citadel, since her powers, invisibility and telekinesis, seems not have the corruption drawback as all the others Specials have, and when she remain pregnant, La Divisione ["The Division", organization that control the Citadel for the Russian government] start to hope that she will give a birth to the first "natural born special". They even create a special suit for her, which adapt to her powers.

With the crumble of the Sovient in Russia, the Specials rebel and take the City of Specials, transforming into their revolutionary base. Andreij, Yelena and some others don't accept the new leadership and try to escape, prefering to be free instead than imprisoned under some sort of "Revolutionary Special Leader", but Yelena sacrifice itself for grant escape to Andreij, which was carring into a bag their son (which will became Michele Silenzi, the Invisible Boy, inerheriting her powers).

SPOILER:

At the end of the film and the comics, is shown that Yelena is still alive, and now she lead La Divisione, transformed into a corrupted superpowered mercenary/criminal organization. It's also revealed that she and Andreij have two twing child, not only Michele, but also a missing daughter, hidden by Andreij in Turkey.

NOTE:

The Character have been created by Gabriele Salvatores, Film Director, while Diego Cajelli is the writer of the comic.

IN OTHER MEDIA:

Yelena is played by russian actoress Ksenia Rappoport
name: Yelena
